		<h1>
		eyetrackerInitialise(hostname,portsend,portreceive)<br>
		eyetrackerCalibrate()<br>
		eyetrackerStart(frequency,filename)<br>
		eyetrackerStop()<br>
		eyetrackerTrigger(triggername)
		</h1>

		<div id="abstract">
		BoXS supports SMI eye trackers. This interface was developed in cooperation with the Max Planck Institute for Research on Collective Goods. 
		In order to use it, the SMI main program must run in the background and it must have the so-called remote command interface enabled. 
		Due to the amount of data generated by the eye tracker, the information generated is not stored like other variables within the BoXS. Instead, 
		the data will be exported into a text file which can be analysed and evaluated after the experiment. BoXS allows you to synchronise the eye tracking 
		data and the BoXS data using timestamps and triggers.
		</div>


		<h2>Examples</h2>
