		<div id="note">
		Important: If the client applet fails to save the eye tracking data to a file or complains about it during the process (exception), you need to grant 
		Java applets the right to access local files. In order to do this, you need to edit the java permissions file named java.policy. The location of this file 
		differs and depends on the Java version you have installed and the operating system. <br>Under Windows you can usually find it here: <b>Program Files/Java/jre6/lib/security/java.policy</b><br>For Linux, have a look here: <b>/usr/lib/jvm/java-6-openjdk-amd64/jre/lib/security/java.policy</b><br>Once you have found the file edit it and insert this line into the Grant-block: <br> <b>permission java.io.FilePermission "&lt;&lt;ALL FILES&gt;&gt;","write";</b><br>
		This should solve the file-saving issue. 
		</div>

